org.azyva.dragom.jenkins

Interface JenkinsClient.Build

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultJenkinsClientImpl.DefaultBuildImpl
    Enclosing interface:
    JenkinsClient

    public static interface JenkinsClient.Build
    Represents a build.

    Instances are created by JenkinsClient.build(java.lang.String, java.util.Map<java.lang.String, java.lang.String>).

    Allows getting information about the build while it progresses to completion.

      • cancel

        boolean cancel()
        Cancels or aborts the build, depending on whether its JenkinsClient.BuildState is JenkinsClient.BuildState.QUEUED or JenkinsClient.BuildState.RUNNING.

        A build in any other BuildState cannot be cancelled and false is returned.

        Returns:
        Indicates if the build has been aborted or cancelled successfully. Generally this can be assumed to be true since if an error occurs, an exception is thrown.

      • getNextConsoleChunk

        String getNextConsoleChunk()
        Returns:
        Returns the next chunk of console output or null if not JenkinsClient.BuildState.isOutOfQueue() or if no more data is available.

      • getFullConsole

        String getFullConsole()
        Returns:
        Complete console output or null if not JenkinsClient.BuildState.isOutOfQueue().
